Alexander Gallo Holdings Files for Bankruptcy in New York

-- B y   D a w n   M c C a r t y
-- 
2011-09-07T16:48:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-07/alexander-gallo-holdings-files-for-bankruptcy-in-new-york-1-.html
Alexander Gallo Holdings LLC , a
provider of court reporting and litigation services, filed for
 bankruptcy protection .  The company today listed debt in the range of $100 million
to $500 million and assets of less than $100 million in Chapter
11 documents in U.S. Bankruptcy Court in Manhattan.  The company and its unitsâ€™ 30 largest creditors without
collateral backing their claims are owed about $189 million,
according to court documents. Gallo Holdings LLC, listed as the
note holder representative, is the biggest, with a claim of
$147.9 million, according to court papers.  Peachtree Holdings Inc. holds 100 percent of the equity
interest in the Atlanta-based company. Ten affiliates, including
Esquire Solutions and Esquire Litigation Solutions, also sought
protection.  The case is In re Alexander Gallo Holdings LLC, 11-14220,
 U.S. Bankruptcy Court , Southern District of  New York 
(Manhattan).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Dawn McCarty in Wilmington, Delaware,
